      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MISS ELPHABA (2) is a good beginner but will need a quick break. Last start finished 2nd on February 21 over 400m at this track behind Rhapsody Beast beaten 2.75 lengths (23.13) in a Grade 5. Looks suited and should go close. EADER (1) filled a minor placing last start at Taree Super Track behind Tangles Tippett (17.67) in a Grade 5. Settled off speed and worked to the line nicely. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Must be included in calculations. WRECK IT REX (8) chased the lead early from the inside and boxed on well to finish second, beaten 0.8 lengths (19.95) at Gunnedah in a Grade 4 over 340m. Has performed well from this box with a win and five minor placings to his name from 10 starts. Can measure up. LIGNITE COAL (5) was well fancied last time on the strength of a win two back but could only manage fifth (23.56) at this track. Good beginner but will need a little luck from a middle draw.",
